main event: A bright white object, slightly brighter than Venus, was observed traveling at a fantastic speed with a smoke trail of about 30 degrees in Walcott, Iowa on November 18, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as traveling at a fantastic speed and having a smoke trail of about 30 degrees.
The observer initially reported seeing the object at 5:15 PM on November 17, but later indicated it was at 6:15 PM on November 18.
The object was concluded to likely be a fireball or bright meteor.
The observer reported the object as being slightly brighter than the planet Venus.
No photographs of the object were included in the report.
